Nov 1 2009 	Awesome stay at Hotel Vitale	We had an early morning fligh from Newark to San Francisco . We landed at 10:30, retrieved our luggage and got a taxi at the taxi stand to take us to the Hotel Vitale, which cost $46 with tip. We were at the hotel by 11:15 and our room was ready by 11:30. They upgraded us, without us even asking, to a waterview room. The staff was so friendly and went out of their way for us. The bell hop brought our bags to our room and after all that we still had time to walk across the street to catch the 12:00 ferry to Sausalito. Could not believe how well that timing worked out. The views from the ferry were magnificent. We stayed in Sausalito for a little bit walking around, soaking in the view and eating lunch. The kids were getting tired, so we caught the ferry back and walked around the ferry building which is filled with different foods and wares and just a great place to visit. We went back to the hotel to rest up a little bit and then off to the Giants game. It was about a 20 minute walk to ATT Park along the Embarcadero. The park is beautiful and the game was great. We walked back to the hotel, as did many others from the game, and felt very safe. The gym at the hotel was nothing to talk about, just a few machines, nothing special. the rooms were very modern and clean and the beds were extremely comfortable. In the morning they had coffee set up in the lobby and it was very comfy to sit around on the couches in the lobby reading the paper. There was a restaurant in the hotel and were going to go there for breakfast, but someone had recommended Mel's Diner on 4th and Mission, so we took a walk over there. The food was delicious and the portions were huge. Each meal cost about $10, but well worth it, considering none of us were hungry till dinner. I would highly recommend the Hotel Vitale and San Francisco!	
