Oct 12 2009 	Luxe by the Bay	Stayed here for 5 nights as part of a mini &quot;road trip&quot;. (See also Yosemite View Lodge and Carmel Mission Inn).Had a city deluxe room, large and airy, high quality furnishings, plasma TV, I pod docking staion and enormous comfy bed. Decent sized luxury bathroom with shower and (small) bath. There were even recycling facilities in the room, with one wastebin just for recycled items!All staff were friendly and helpful, and we made good use of the concierge for transport queries and other recommendations. The hotel is right next to the bay, on the edge of the financial district. 15 mins (mainly flat!) walk to Union Square. Start of cable car on Market St is just around the corner.Didn't eat at the hotel (or use the bar, which was always packed.)Only slight negatives were that although the room was on the 5th floor, it was noisy from very early (05.00 ish) in the morning, with road noise, trolley buses etc. Probably didn't wake me up, but made it difficult getting back to sleep. There was very limited cupboard / storage space in the room: no doubt loads of guests are just there for one or two nights, but I'm sure we weren't the first people to have stayed at the beginning of a 2 week trip, and wanting to unpack! Although a &quot;turndown&quot; service was mentioned , we didn't get this during our stay.We got a 3 day MUNI Pass (18$) which you can use on cable car, street cars, BART and the trolleybuses. This is great value as one journey on the cable car is $5 and on the buses etc $2.The Ferry building over the road is a gastronomic paradise, with loads of specialist food shops, some restaurants and farmers' markets 4 times a week.Ferry building recommendations:Boulette's Larder for breakfast, excellent burgers at Taylor's Automatic Refresher, good Mexican at Mijita, The Slanted Door - great Vietnamese food. NB Difficult to get in as usually fully booked, but get there at 5 ish and ask if there are any walk ins. (Managed to be first in the line the evening we went!)Mijita was good, but check out closing times! We got there just after 7 one evening,ordered starter and first margarita, went back 10 mins later for more margaritas and main course and the kitchen had closed with no warning given to punters this was about to happen!All in all enjoyed our stay there and would return.	
