Feb 10 2009	Basically very goo.	Hotel Vitale, San Franciso 12/31/08-1/5/09It was a real treat to spend 5 nights at Hotel Vitale. The location was delightful: on The Embarcadero, opposite The Ferry Building, a couple of blocks from the California St. cable car and a 15 minute walk to Union Square, There were also many fine restaurants we could walk to in addition to Americano, the excellent restaurant in the hotel.The room we had was a notch or two larger than I expected. The décor was very boutique-hotel, with restful pale blue added to the usual beiges and browns. A long wooden unit contained generous desk space, the mini bar, some storage and an extensive selection of snacks, candies etc. for sale. (I always immediately put these in a drawer or the closet shelf. I don’t like the clutter or the temptation.) A chaise longue near the window was a great place to watch the constant traffic of ships gliding under the Bay Bridge just outside. The bathroom was rather lame for such a deluxe hotel…Painted sheetrock wall, a nondescript (well, it was squarish) counter sink, not great lighting. Actually it wasn’t deluxe at all. I had major internet issues that could not be fixed even after long conversations with the tech crew in Georgia. If good internet connection is important to you, sign up for the costly premium connection when you first arrive. It was impossible for me to switch once I had signed up for five days. Definitely a flaw. If it had been a working trip, I probably would have had to go to another hotel. Joie de Vivre should offer acceptable free internet service…Or not bother with free service.That said, the staff did their best. We had a note and wine and lots of sympathy from the front desk crew. It’s a wonderful hotel that I can enthusiastically recommend with that one craveat.	
