Dec 19 2007	Have found my "San Francisco Hotel"	I chose the Hotel Vitale for its location - across the street from the Ferry Building and the open air farmer's market. Location is reason enough to return.The bonus is the hotel itself - welcoming and friendly, yet professional and detail focused. During check-in the front desk volunteered to move me to a higher floor and a spectacular view the next day when a sixth floor room became available. From the second day on the valets remembered my car. A bellman showed me where the ice machine was hidden so I wouldn't have to call for ice. Everyone was determined to provide service above and beyond... and they did.My room was impeccable. The rain-shower in the bathroom, awesome. My one room service order served promptly, hot and well prepared.A minor complaint that I hope the Hotel Vitale management will consider. The hotel offers free internet service and free it is. Also slow. They offer an upgrade to high speed for $9.95 a day. Charge a little more for the room and throw in the high speed internet and I won't complain. Offer me free internet and then nickel dime me for decent speed internet and I take issue. One other nit - a hip hotel like this and no Comedy Channel on the cable line-up for the Daily Show or Cobert Report? Hopefully there will be a new internet policy when I return next spring. Either way I will be returning on a regular basis.	
Nov 22 2007 	A Great Relaxing Hotel 	We stayed at Hotel Vitale on our way to our honeymoon in Hawaii. This place was a great stop to get us relaxed and ready to go!Room - Very zen and calm feeling. Loved the 'Fresh' lemon sugar body lotions, soaps, soy shampoo, pomegranate conditioner. Complimentary terry robes, slipper, water &amp; chocolates at turndown. The bed is super comfy, used the iPod dock/alarm clock - which was a nice touch. We also received a free bottle of sparkling wine (from Napa of course) and rose petals scattered into heart from housekeeping, along with a card and a complimentary cold eye mask - since we would be travelling on to Hawaii. The place is really clean and the building is only a couple years old. Very hip, but more relaxed - reminds me a bit of the W. Seems like a lot of business travellers, the place is pretty empty during the day. They also had a free downtown car service, but it was booked when we tried to use it.Business Centre - Free computers &amp; internet usage with 3 workstations! I always like this.Green Roof - What a fantastic initiative! Grass on the roof with sleek outdoor lounge furniture to watch the sunset or to have a drink. I truly felt relaxed up here.Service - Didn't have any major problem with the service, no complimentary hot towel upon check-in...they missed us. As well, someone was going to call when our room was ready - since we were early and never did. Breakfast/Room Service - Absolutely delicious! Order the Eggs Benedict w/ Proscuitto and you won't be disappointed. Quick &amp; courteous, not particularily overpriced.Location - Fantastic! Head to the Ferry Building upon arrival for a late lunch or a snack. Highly recommend Dim Sum @ Yank Sing in the Rinocon Centre (5 mins. away). We are from Toronto and were blown away by the quality/service here - a local favourite. If you fly in from SFO - take the BART train to Embracadero station for $5.15. It takes 30 minutes and you can walk from the stop to the hotel. I loved this because I hate to sit in traffic...the BART was very efficient.All in all a great experience, I'm also surprised that this place doesn't have a higher ranking. We would definitely stay here again!	
Nov 12 2007 	Not A Good Value!	We spent a night last weekend at the Hotel Vitale. The location is great -- across the street from the Embarcadero &amp; the Ferry Building/farmer's market. We took long walks -- to North Beach and Coit Tower in the morning, and to Union Square in the afternoon. The hotel has a hipster feel, and nice design -- although the bar was crowded with a large tour group of some sort on Saturday afternoon. The rooms are stocked with soap, shampoo, and lotion by Fresh, which we loved. Overall, however, we were not very impressed with the service and feel of the hotel. Most glaringly, we were awakened in the middle of the night by two telephone calls -- both times the line went dead when we picked up the phone. When we called the front desk to find out what was going on, the manager haughtily told us he was trying to check another party into our room and they had no record of us ever checking in. &quot;What is your name?&quot; he demanded. When we told him, he said he had no record of us signing the check-in card. Again, he told us that other people were trying to check into our room, but that the hotel computer would not allow him to check them in. Sleepily, we tried to make sense of all this -- and were finally able to disengage, but it was upsetting in the middle of the night. We had a hard time getting back to sleep! The next morning, when we asked for an extra half hour after check-out, we were given a firm &quot;no.&quot; I wouldn't stay here again, and for the price, one might expect a nicer attitude.	
