Aug 6 2007 	Hip Comfort in the heart of the Embarcadero	We met up in San Francisco with some other out-of-town family members at the Hotel Vitale who were also in town for business. I did some research and wound up choosing this hotel as a great location that would be pleasing to all the varying tastes of all those involved... a motley crew of varied ages, ethnicities, genders, budgets and interests. Surprisingly EVERYONE WAS SATISFIED!!The location was absolutely perfect for getting around the Embarcadero on foot. Several wonderful restaurants were just steps away… (particularly the pricey, but OH, so worth it! One Market). If it’s raining or you just don’t feel like straying too far from the comfort of the hotel, the on-site restaurant Americano is an excellent choice for great food, too. In fact rolling out of bed and grabbing a decent breakfast in the area is quite difficult so I would strongly recommend doing so at Americano. Just make sure you get there before they stop serving it (at 10:30AM). Americano is also a great location for lunch &amp; dinner. Anyone looking to have an intimate conversation or trying to bring together a group of people should know that this place gets LOUD, crowded, and “sceney” as the night gets going. Apparently reservations are strongly recommended too, as this is a quite the HIP LOCALE for locals as well. So don’t be surprised to come down from your room on any given night and find a virtual night-club scene going on. And those who are waiting to get in tend to linger in the lobby. This was not a nuisance to me as a guest, but it could be to some. Also the noise didn’t affect my stay there at all either, so no worries there.The room was beautiful… stunning really. Even the concave window added to the uniqueness of the room. The bed was incredibly comfortable, and the staff turned on soothing ambient music with the Turn-Down service each night, leaving a little quote or poem on our pillow.And now the reason I chose our Urban Studio room… THE DEEP SOAKING TUB! Wow! So worth the experience! I absolutely looked forward to my evening soaks, and made sure to let them last as long as possible. After all with a tub that deep, the water seems to stay warm forever, and why get out at all unless necessary? I should caution against the “Privacy Factor”, as there really is none. The tub is practically in the room. It’s actually sort of “just around the corner” and not in a separate bathroom. So I do hope you are really close with your fellow traveler (i.e. LOVER/SPOUSE/SIGNIFICANT OTHER – “CLOSE”).Did I love it? Yes! And I even got kudos from each of my other family members for the choice. Would I or any of them stay there again? You betcha!! Great décor, superb comfort &amp; pampering, amazing food, and very personable and friendly costumer service, all for a surprisingly budget-friendly price… and in one of the most beautiful cities in the U.S… who could ask for anything more??!!	
